02:15.668 --> 02:19.406
the individuals charged with criminal offenses. Included in

02:19.428 --> 02:23.122
these mandates are the right to a jury trial, equal access to

02:23.176 --> 02:26.754
the legal system, and adherence to our state and local law.

02:26.952 --> 02:28.260
Next slide, please.

02:33.850 --> 02:37.346
Sorry. Oh. Next slide,

02:37.378 --> 02:41.334
please. MCD has

02:41.372 --> 02:45.438
many internal revenue generating initiatives that provide enhanced

02:45.474 --> 02:48.934
court services to the public and assist municipal courts

02:48.982 --> 02:53.094
in achieving its overall revenue target. These services include

02:53.142 --> 02:56.614
passports, weddings notary, and the printing of driving

02:56.662 --> 03:00.590
records to better serve target areas within our community.

03:00.740 --> 03:04.426
We have various specialized dockets that provide meaningful

03:04.538 --> 03:07.034
and safe methods for case resolution,

03:07.162 --> 03:10.602
including the Veterans Court and the Safe Harbor Court.

03:10.746 --> 03:14.542
Judges assigned to these dockets have the ability to reduce fines,

03:14.606 --> 03:18.414
offer payment plans, or other methods of case resolution

03:18.462 --> 03:21.634
to individuals who are experiencing hardships but who

03:21.672 --> 03:24.882
still want to fulfill their legal obligations to the court.

03:25.026 --> 03:28.694
I'm happy to report that Teen Court was able to resume their

03:28.732 --> 03:32.774
in person monthly activities in FY 22. This program

03:32.892 --> 03:37.046
has made long lasting impressions on the lives of our youth by providing

03:37.078 --> 03:40.934
a glimpse at the legal system through firsthand participation

03:41.062 --> 03:44.838
and through mentorship provided by our professional volunteers.

03:44.934 --> 03:48.494
Next slide, please. I think

03:48.532 --> 03:52.126
we're one slide ahead of me now. There we

03:52.148 --> 03:55.742
go. MCD began decentralizing court services

03:55.876 --> 03:59.166
many years ago, anticipating the future growth in

03:59.188 --> 04:02.546
the population. We serve our full service courts can

04:02.568 --> 04:06.494
be found in key areas of the city and they include our central

04:06.542 --> 04:09.774
location, Macawa, West Side and North

04:09.822 --> 04:13.250
Command. We also have annex courts that are open

04:13.320 --> 04:16.662
and located in Kingwood and the Clear Lake areas which are open

04:16.716 --> 04:20.034
one day per week, and a court at the Joint Processing

04:20.082 --> 04:24.066
Center which we perform and they handle jail, dockets and magistrate

04:24.098 --> 04:27.706
court services, and we do those. That court is in

04:27.728 --> 04:30.442
operation seven days a week, 22 hours a day,

04:30.496 --> 04:34.454
365 days a year. We also anticipated

04:34.502 --> 04:38.382
the greater use of technology and have implemented many web

04:38.436 --> 04:41.678
based processes. Our short term messaging service

04:41.764 --> 04:45.214
provides text messages and email reminders to our

04:45.252 --> 04:48.574
customers about upcoming scheduled court dates, as well

04:48.612 --> 04:52.210
as important emergency notifications to address

04:52.280 --> 04:56.434
the needs of our diverse community and to allow full participation in the

04:56.472 --> 05:00.062
legal service. We have full time certified Spanish

05:00.126 --> 05:04.002
interpreters as well as access to other languages through contract

05:04.066 --> 05:07.480
services and the language line. Next slide, please.

05:09.770 --> 05:13.522
This slide represents a comparison of revenue for FY

05:13.586 --> 05:17.066
21, FY 22 and FY 23 for

05:17.088 --> 05:20.218
all MCD funds and the percentage change

05:20.304 --> 05:24.330
between the FY 23 proposed and the FY 22

05:24.400 --> 05:28.826
estimates. As reflected, there is an overall 3% decrease

05:28.858 --> 05:32.270
in revenue across all funds for FY 23.

05:32.420 --> 05:36.490
Next slide, please. Despite the COVID challenges

05:36.570 --> 05:40.234
and the lower rate of citation issuance, we expect FY

05:40.282 --> 05:43.586
22 General Fund revenues to exceed the

05:43.608 --> 05:47.266
budget target. This increase is attributed to the resumption of

05:47.288 --> 05:51.374
all the dockets, including cases that were delayed during the suspension

05:51.422 --> 05:54.934
period. This increase is also due to the high level of

05:54.972 --> 05:58.466
performance from our internal and external collection teams,

05:58.578 --> 06:02.306
McD's revenue generated initiatives, and the deferred

06:02.338 --> 06:05.510
payment program for FY 23.

