Next slide, please. The MCD

10:14.546 --> 10:18.634
organizational chart on this slide includes our leadership team and

10:18.672 --> 10:23.050
lines of direct and indirect reporting. Next slide.

10:24.510 --> 10:28.774
The information provided here reflects the diversity of our municipal court

10:28.822 --> 10:30.960
team. Next slide, please.

10:32.370 --> 10:36.122
I am pleased to be able to share with you some of our major accomplishments

10:36.186 --> 10:39.754
from this past year on the next two slides. While we remained

10:39.802 --> 10:43.134
operational throughout COVID Pandemic, we suspended

10:43.182 --> 10:46.610
regular dockets and jury service for over a year.

10:46.760 --> 10:50.354
This resulted in a large number of our cases that needed to be

10:50.392 --> 10:53.874
reset and rescheduled. We have worked diligently

10:54.002 --> 10:57.974
since then, resuming dockets from last April to reschedule these

10:58.012 --> 11:01.670
cases, handle the volume of new cases, and maintain lower

11:01.740 --> 11:05.514
docket levels to meet safe distancing requirements. We also

11:05.552 --> 11:08.982
summoned jurors at a reduced level and found a solution

11:09.046 --> 11:12.346
for masking by implementing a clear mask option for

11:12.368 --> 11:16.394
the jurors selected for trials. Our Passport program

11:16.512 --> 11:19.690
is celebrating its first year anniversary.

11:19.770 --> 11:23.406
To date, our Passport program has assisted almost 3000

11:23.508 --> 11:27.082
individuals to obtain their passports and has generated

11:27.146 --> 11:30.062
$115,000 in that year.

11:30.196 --> 11:34.366
I'm extremely proud of our staff who has worked very hard to obtain their certification

11:34.478 --> 11:37.666
as passport agents and their dedication to the

11:37.688 --> 11:41.506
success of our program. Our program has been recognized by

11:41.528 --> 11:45.206
the US. Department of State for excellent customer service and

11:45.228 --> 11:49.078
for increasing the availability of this public service.

11:49.244 --> 11:53.270
Next slide. In order to better serve

11:53.690 --> 11:57.610
our other areas of our community, the Juvenile Case Manager Program

11:57.760 --> 12:01.126
expanded its Truancy prevention services to include

12:01.158 --> 12:04.666
the Aldine Independent School District this past year.

12:04.848 --> 12:08.582
Our Deferred Payment Program was recently recognized

12:08.646 --> 12:12.526
by the Government Collections Association of Texas as being the

12:12.548 --> 12:16.302
most innovative collection program for 2021.

12:16.436 --> 12:20.194
This program has a great team of dedicated staff who work very

12:20.232 --> 12:24.194
closely with individuals who need time to pay their fines and who

12:24.232 --> 12:27.038
track cases through the successful compliance.

12:27.214 --> 12:31.182
Court security remains at the forefront in our today's challenging

12:31.246 --> 12:35.026
environment. McD's Court Security Committee

12:35.138 --> 12:39.138
includes broad range of internal and external participants,

12:39.234 --> 12:42.242
and we meet monthly to discuss security related

12:42.306 --> 12:46.246
issues. Next slide, please. The major unmet

12:46.278 --> 12:49.466
need for MCD is the

12:49.488 --> 12:52.886
replacement of our central facility. We suffered

12:52.918 --> 12:57.020
major damage from Hurricane Harvey almost five years ago.

12:57.410 --> 13:01.102
Our court staff has been extremely flexible and

13:01.156 --> 13:04.394
several workarounds have been implemented, including doubling

13:04.442 --> 13:08.426
up in courts, doubling up in offices, sharing workspaces,

13:08.538 --> 13:12.078
and dealing with additional flooding and infrastructure

13:12.254 --> 13:16.098
failures as they arise and occur throughout the building.

13:16.264 --> 13:19.950
We are currently working very closely with the Mayor, GSD,

13:20.030 --> 13:23.366
Finance and FEMA to find a permanent solution for

13:23.388 --> 13:27.314
this ongoing facility replacement project. Next slide,

13:27.362 --> 13:30.886
please. This concludes the presentation of our

13:30.908 --> 13:34.466
FY 23 budget. Just wanted to thank my entire court

13:34.498 --> 13:37.734
team. They have been resilient and positive throughout this

13:37.772 --> 13:41.734
entire five years, doing the things that were necessary to keep the courts

13:41.782 --> 13:44.950
up, to keep the courts running, to keep the courts operational,

13:45.110 --> 13:48.394
and they have been doing an excellent job. And I would also

13:48.432 --> 13:51.914
like to thank the mayor, all of you council members for your continued

13:51.962 --> 13:54.714
support and my partner departments as GSD.

13:54.842 --> 13:58.110
Sometimes they let me knock out a wall, sometimes they won't.

13:58.530 --> 14:02.602
But we have done everything we can to keep the courts at the central location

14:02.666 --> 14:06.370
up and running for our citizens of Houston. And at this time, I welcome

14:06.440 --> 14:10.750
any questions you have. Thank you. Judge, do you have any insight

14:10.830 --> 14:15.094
on our site and release initiative? How many cases come

14:15.132 --> 14:17.800
to courts based on the site and release program?

14:18.490 --> 14:20.440
Site and release? Yes.

14:23.210 --> 14:27.222
They never come to municipal court for Class C misdemeanors?

14:27.286 --> 14:29.820
No, sir. Okay.

14:30.670 --> 14:34.326
All right. What about the associate judges positions?

14:34.358 --> 14:38.022
Have we filled those or how are we looking for the Associate

14:38.086 --> 14:41.678
municipal court judges? We are still going through the

14:41.684 --> 14:45.786
boards of commission to see who is applying. To date, we really don't

14:45.818 --> 14:49.386
have very many applicants because we are looking for more applicants

14:49.418 --> 14:52.994
for the Associate Judge position. I think I

14:53.032 --> 14:56.226
have contacted Jackie and the

14:56.248 --> 14:59.534
newest person there who took Maria's place, and we're

14:59.582 --> 15:03.140
still trying to get applicants in. If you could send

15:03.910 --> 15:07.794
additional information to my office again like you all did earlier

15:07.842 --> 15:11.286
in the year so we can reach out to our networks to see if

15:11.308 --> 15:16.518
we can get some people to apply, we'll do great council

15:16.534 --> 15:19.610
Member Abby Cayman. Thank you, Vice Chair.

15:20.430 --> 15:23.866
Judge, I think you've spotlighted all of the

15:23.888 --> 15:27.614
challenges that the municipal courts continue to face, again,

15:27.652 --> 15:30.190
distinct from criminal and civil.

15:30.930 --> 15:34.958
But going back to the accomplishments you listed, I know when

15:34.964 --> 15:38.634
we've been talking at Public Safety Committee night court,

15:38.762 --> 15:40.030
team court,

15:42.070 --> 15:45.954
all of the different efforts to meet people where

15:45.992 --> 15:50.354
they are, make sure they aren't unduly penalized and

15:50.392 --> 15:53.954
do right by them and do right by the city and law enforcement.

15:54.002 --> 15:58.614
Right. So I just want to give you all credit for that really

15:58.652 --> 16:01.560
quickly on the building, because you mentioned that.

16:03.130 --> 16:06.540
Talk to us about some of those challenges, if you can. Again,

16:06.990 --> 16:10.550
we are still dealing with the impacts of Harvey

16:10.710 --> 16:13.882
COVID, the structural damage. But what is that doing

16:13.936 --> 16:17.706
to the court process? The ability to function day to

16:17.728 --> 16:21.246
day. When Harvey hit, it wiped out the

16:21.268 --> 16:24.574
entire basement, as everybody knows. And we had six

16:24.612 --> 16:27.962
courts, I think, in operation. We had a bonding section,

16:28.026 --> 16:31.726
parking section, the bailiffs, we had different offices there.

16:31.828 --> 16:34.960
So all of those offices had to move

16:35.570 --> 16:39.162
somewhere. And the only court we had on the first floor

16:39.226 --> 16:43.320
was one court. And we have all of the cashiers and

16:43.770 --> 16:47.266
their departments there. The second floor had courtrooms.

16:47.378 --> 16:50.822
And so we have staff that we have

16:50.876 --> 16:55.500
renovated closets to put supervisors in.

16:57.630 --> 17:01.030
We have judges that are doubling up with courts and court dockets.

17:01.110 --> 17:05.914
We have done everything we could to maintain the

17:05.952 --> 17:09.450
atmosphere of a court that's friendly and safe for everyone.

17:09.600 --> 17:13.642
And then came COVID. And with COVID you can't

17:13.706 --> 17:17.134
stand close to each other. So it took the limited amount

17:17.172 --> 17:20.494
of space we had in the courtroom and cut it in half.

17:20.692 --> 17:24.594
And so that's how we have been operating now,

17:24.712 --> 17:28.274
but we're opening back up into sitting next to each other.

17:28.312 --> 17:31.486
But I have been mandated by the Supreme Court

17:31.518 --> 17:35.454
and I've given the authority to have everyone wear a mask

17:35.502 --> 17:38.694
because we see 2000, 3000 people a day. I just

17:38.732 --> 17:42.294
think it's safer that way for the employees. And I appreciate that

17:42.332 --> 17:46.186
because more shutdowns are going to create a further backlog. So I

17:46.208 --> 17:49.340
completely get that really quickly.

17:50.270 --> 17:53.500
In terms of other needs, concerns for the future,

17:54.270 --> 17:59.002
talk to me about truancy prevention and how that's going. Our truancy

17:59.146 --> 18:02.846
prevention is basically we have

18:02.868 --> 18:06.382
a fund from we have grant funding and we started out

18:06.436 --> 18:11.410
with grant funding that was around the $700,000

18:11.480 --> 18:15.102
range. We have seven juvenile case managers that operate

18:15.166 --> 18:19.502
under that grant. We have now submitted

18:19.646 --> 18:23.090
a request for additional grants and right now

18:23.160 --> 18:26.990
it's pending approval temporarily.

18:27.070 --> 18:31.398
They're saying that we may get 100,000. If we just get 100,000.

18:31.564 --> 18:34.966
There may be some other options we have to have to go to do so.

18:34.988 --> 18:38.554
That is an unmet need because for the school district to

18:38.592 --> 18:42.426
have juvenile case managers in there who know the

18:42.448 --> 18:45.946
kids if they come to teen court, the defendants who come to

18:45.968 --> 18:49.450
teen court, chances are a juvenile case manager

18:49.530 --> 18:53.440
knows that kid. And if we have to cut it,

18:53.890 --> 18:57.550
it's going to be a disservice, I think, to our youth.

18:57.890 --> 19:02.018
I just received word on the way yesterday to

19:02.104 --> 19:05.298
Teen Court's final thing that I do believe.

19:05.464 --> 19:09.060
I don't know if he is my first, but one of the first

19:09.510 --> 19:13.018
juveniles student volunteers that came through Teen

19:13.054 --> 19:16.326
Court is about to graduate from the University of Houston's Law

19:16.348 --> 19:18.840
School. So I was very proud of that.

19:19.290 --> 19:22.150
But if the Juvenile case managers,

19:23.450 --> 19:26.886
if we have enough money to keep what

19:26.908 --> 19:30.154
we have, we can work. But I'm not really sure we're going to be able

19:30.192 --> 19:33.430
to keep what we have with just that amount of grant funding.

19:33.510 --> 19:36.746
So are you saying that we may lose the 700,000 that

19:36.768 --> 19:40.762
we currently have? 700,000 is what they started

19:40.816 --> 19:45.566
off giving us. Then we went down to 500 and

19:45.588 --> 19:48.000
now the proposed is 125,

19:49.250 --> 19:53.060
I think you're saying is the Truancy program as is cannot continue.

19:53.750 --> 19:57.314
We have seven JCMS that are funded there. We may be able

19:57.352 --> 19:59.890
to fund three, but four we may lose.

20:00.230 --> 20:03.000
If you could keep us apprised of that,

20:03.770 --> 20:05.800
